name: Identifiable Name or Title
description: Full name, title, or identifiable part of an individual (e.g., first name, last name, user name, title).
examples: Hi John Smith, thanks for your inquiry.
The CEO has approved the request.
Hello, my name is Peter Jennings.

name: Identification TimeDate
description: Dates or times that identify or verify a person, including birth dates, document issue dates, or identity-related timestamps.

name: Identification Number
description: Unique identifiers assigned to individuals such as Social Security numbers, passport numbers, or national IDs.

name: Phone Number
description: Any phone number used to identify or contact an individual.

name: Credential Information
description: Information used to access systems or accounts, such as passwords, PINs, or security questions.

name: Location Data
description: Information about a person’s location such as address, GPS coordinates, or city of residence.
examples: I live at 123 Baker Street, London.
Property address: 1452 Grand Ave, Brooklyn, NY

name: Online Identifier
description: Digital identifiers like IP addresses, MAC addresses, cookies, or browser/device fingerprints.

name: Email Address
description: Email addresses that can be used to identify or contact a person.

name: Sex Life or Sexual Orientation
description: Information about an individual's sexual orientation or sexual activity.

name: Geopolitical Entities
description: Information revealing national origin, citizenship, or geopolitical affiliation.
examples: The new Namibian government has issued a statement.
He joined the European Workers' Union.
Studies conducted in the Israeli health system.

name: [WARN] Statistical Data
description: Numerical or statistical information that may be linked to individuals or groups.
examples: Company said profit fell 49% to $23.5 million.
Between 6.5% and 7.5% of users reported issues.
10 out of 100 patients experienced side effects.

name: [WARN] Money Data
description: Monetary values or financial transactions tied to individuals.
examples: Profit of around $17 million last quarter.

name: [DELETE] Cardinal or Quantity Number
description: Numerical quantities not necessarily tied to money, such as counts or measurements.

name: [NOT FOUND] Genetic Data
description: Data relating to inherited or acquired genetic characteristics, often from DNA testing.
examples: The DNA test revealed a rare gene mutation.
Father and child matched on 21 loci.

name: [NOT FOUND] Health Data
description: Information related to an individual's physical or mental health.
examples: She was diagnosed with diabetes last year.
Symptoms include chronic fatigue and migraines.

name: Racial or Ethnic Origin
description: Information that reveals a person's racial or ethnic background.
examples: Native American background noted in file

name: [NOT FOUND] Political Opinions
description: Statements or information related to political beliefs, party affiliation, or ideology.
examples: She is a member of the Green Party.
I voted for the Socialist candidate.

name: [NOT FOUND] Religious or Philosophical Beliefs
description: Information about religious affiliation or personal belief systems.
examples: As a Christian, he attends church weekly.

name: [NOT FOUND] Criminal Convictions
description: Information regarding criminal records, arrests, or legal judgments.
examples: He was convicted of theft in 2018.
She was arrested for fraud last year.
